==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Steinbock
<hw>Stein"bock`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G.
<ets>stein</ets> stone + <ets>bock</ets> buck, D. <ets>bok</ets>. Cf.
<er>Steenbok</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
European ibex.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>A small South African antelope
(<spn>Nanotragus tragulus</spn>) which frequents dry, rocky districts;
-- called also <altname>steenbok</altname>.</def> <altsp>[Written also
<asp>steinboc</asp>, and <asp>steinbok</asp>; also called
<asp>stonebock</asp>, and <asp>stonebuck</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Steingale</ent>⟦br⟧
